Alcohol by volume (ABV) pattern

  • Intersted in: what category/brewer/style of beer has the most Alcohol by volume (ABV)?

By category

cat_abv = 
  beer %>% 
  replace_na(list(category = "NA", y = "unknown")) %>% 
  group_by(category) %>% 
  summarise(mean_abv = mean(alcohol_by_volume)) %>% 
  arrange(desc(mean_abv)) 
## `summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)
cat_abv
## # A tibble: 9 x 2
##   category               mean_abv
##   <chr>                     <dbl>
## 1 Belgian and French Ale     6.50
## 2 British Ale                4.40
## 3 Other Style                3.82
## 4 North American Ale         3.40
## 5 German Lager               2.96
## 6 German Ale                 2.67
## 7 Irish Ale                  2.39
## 8 NA                         2.38
## 9 North American Lager       1.75

cat_abv %>% 
  mutate(category = fct_reorder(category, mean_abv)) %>% 
  plot_ly(x = ~category, y = ~mean_abv, color = ~category, type = "bar", colors = "viridis")
## Warning: `arrange_()` is deprecated as of dplyr 0.7.0.
## Please use `arrange()` instead.
## See vignette('programming') for more help
## This warning is displayed once every 8 hours.
## Call `lifecycle::last_warnings()` to see where this warning was generated.

beer %>% 
  mutate(category = fct_reorder(category, alcohol_by_volume)) %>% 
  plot_ly(y = ~alcohol_by_volume, color = ~category, type = "box", colors = "viridis")

By brewer

  • Top 20
brewer_abv = 
  beer %>% 
  group_by(brewer) %>% 
  summarise(mean_abv = mean(alcohol_by_volume)) %>% 
  arrange(desc(mean_abv))
## `summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)
brewer_abv
## # A tibble: 823 x 2
##    brewer                        mean_abv
##    <chr>                            <dbl>
##  1 Mendocino Brewing - Ukiah        10.5 
##  2 Avery Brewing Company            10.5 
##  3 Foothills Brewing Company        10   
##  4 Dogfish Head Craft Brewery        9.78
##  5 Voodoo Brewing Co.,LLC            9.60
##  6 High Point Wheat Beer Company     9.5 
##  7 Brewery Vivant                    9.25
##  8 Oso                               9.20
##  9 Oregon Trail Brewery              9.10
## 10 Independence Brewing Co           9   
## # ... with 813 more rows

brewer_abv %>% 
  slice(1:20) %>% 
  mutate(brewer = fct_reorder(brewer, mean_abv)) %>%
  plot_ly(x = ~brewer, y = ~mean_abv, color = ~brewer, type = "bar", colors = "viridis") %>% 
  layout(yaxis = list(range = c(8, 11)))

top_20_brewer = brewer_abv %>% slice(1:20) %>% select(brewer) %>% unlist()
beer %>% 
  filter(brewer %in% top_20_brewer) %>% 
  mutate(brewer = fct_reorder(brewer, alcohol_by_volume)) %>% 
  plot_ly(y = ~alcohol_by_volume, color = ~brewer, type = "box", colors = "viridis")

By style

  • Top 20
style_abv = 
  beer %>% 
  group_by(style) %>% 
  summarise(mean_abv = mean(alcohol_by_volume)) %>% 
  arrange(desc(mean_abv))
## `summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)
style_abv
## # A tibble: 62 x 2
##    style                             mean_abv
##    <chr>                                <dbl>
##  1 Belgian-Style Quadrupel              11.7 
##  2 Strong Ale                           11.2 
##  3 American-Style Barley Wine Ale        9.96
##  4 American-Style Imperial Stout         9.77
##  5 Belgian-Style Dark Strong Ale         9.67
##  6 Imperial or Double Red Ale            9.20
##  7 Specialty Beer                        8.75
##  8 American-Style India Black Ale        8.70
##  9 Belgian-Style Pale Strong Ale         8.63
## 10 Imperial or Double India Pale Ale     8.58
## # ... with 52 more rows

style_abv %>% 
  slice(1:20) %>% 
  mutate(style = fct_reorder(style, mean_abv)) %>% 
  plot_ly(x = ~style, y = ~mean_abv, color = ~style, type = "bar", colors = "viridis") %>% 
  layout(yaxis = list(range = c(5.5, 12)))

top_20_style = style_abv %>% slice(1:20) %>% select(style) %>% unlist()
beer %>% 
  filter(style %in% top_20_style) %>% 
  mutate(style = fct_reorder(style, alcohol_by_volume)) %>% 
  plot_ly(y = ~alcohol_by_volume, color = ~style, type = "box", colors = "viridis")

By states

beer %>% 
  mutate(state = fct_reorder(state, alcohol_by_volume)) %>% 
  plot_ly(y = ~alcohol_by_volume, color = ~state, type = "box", colors = "viridis")

Location mapping

  • Goal: Map location of each US brewer with category/style, size of marker showing ABV and interactive label showing the tax info by state.

  • map seems not working so well…

pal <- colorNumeric(
  palette = "viridis",
  domain = beer$alcohol_by_volume)

beer %>% 
  na.omit(alcohol_by_volume) %>% 
  mutate(
    click_label = 
      str_c("<b>ABV: ", alcohol_by_volume, 
            "</b><br>City: ", city, 
            "<br>State: ", state, 
            "<br>Country: ", country)) %>% 
  leaflet() %>% 
  addProviderTiles(providers$CartoDB.Positron) %>% 
  addCircleMarkers(~latitude, ~longitude, radius = .1, 
                   color = ~pal(alcohol_by_volume), popup = ~click_label)
  • Map update
    • need to adjust the location display
location_df = 
  beer %>% 
  select(name, latitude, longitude) %>% 
  na.omit()

location <- st_as_sf(location_df, coords = c("longitude", "latitude"), crs = 4326)

mapview(location)
